  "html": "<div class=\"pateressa\"><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Etymology\">Etymology</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=pateressa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Etymology\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><p>From <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"la\"><a href=\"/wiki/pater#Latin\" title=\"pater\">pater</a></i> <span class=\"mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren\">(</span><span class=\"mention-gloss-double-quote\">&#x201C;</span><span class=\"mention-gloss\">father</span><span class=\"mention-gloss-double-quote\">&#x201D;</span><span class=\"mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren\">)</span> +&#x200E; <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"la\"><a href=\"/wiki/-essa#Latin\" title=\"-essa\">-essa</a></i>, a form of <i class=\"Latn mention\" lang=\"la\"><a href=\"/wiki/-issa#Latin\" title=\"-issa\">-issa</a></i> <span class=\"mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren\">(</span><span class=\"mention-gloss-double-quote\">&#x201C;</span><span class=\"mention-gloss\">-ess, female</span><span class=\"mention-gloss-double-quote\">&#x201D;</span><span class=\"mention-gloss-paren annotation-paren\">)</span> (<i>e</i> is frequently used for <i>i</i> at Venosa, where this term is attested).\n</p><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Pronunciation\">Pronunciation</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=pateressa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Pronunciation\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><ul><li><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Classical_Latin\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Classical Latin\">Classical</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet\" title=\"Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet\">IPA</a><sup>(<a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Latin_pronunciation\" title=\"Appendix:Latin pronunciation\">key</a>)</sup>: <span class=\"IPA\">/pa.te&#x2C8;res.sa/</span>, <span class=\"IPA\">[pa.t&#x32A;&#x25B;&#x2C8;&#x27E;&#x25B;s&#x320;.s&#x320;a]</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content qualifier-content\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecclesiastical_Latin\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Ecclesiastical Latin\">Ecclesiastical</a></span><span class=\"ib-brac qualifier-brac\">)</span> <a href=\"/wiki/Wiktionary:International_Phonetic_Alphabet\" title=\"Wiktionary:International Phonetic Alphabet\">IPA</a><sup>(<a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Latin_pronunciation\" title=\"Appendix:Latin pronunciation\">key</a>)</sup>: <span class=\"IPA\">/pa.te&#x2C8;res.sa/</span>, <span class=\"IPA\">[pa.t&#x32A;&#x25B;&#x2C8;r&#x25B;s.sa]</span></li></ul><h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Noun\">Noun</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=pateressa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Noun\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3><p><strong class=\"Latn headword\" lang=\"la\">pateressa</strong>&#xA0;<span class=\"gender\"><abbr title=\"feminine gender\">f</abbr></span>\n</p><ol><li><span class=\"ib-brac\">(</span><span class=\"ib-content\">post-Classical<span class=\"ib-comma\">,</span> Jewish</span><span class=\"ib-brac\">)</span> <span class=\"use-with-mention\">The meaning of this term is uncertain (translated as <i>fatheress</i>).</span>\n<ul><li><div class=\"wiktQuote\" data-validation=\"yellow\"><b>5th&#x2013;early 6th century</b> (epitaph) , (Venosa; <i>in situ</i>: arcosolium D2, grave 8; in Latin and Hebrew; <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.bibliotheque-numerique-aiu.org/viewer/16318/?offset=#page=106\">image</a>;<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup>; <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/item/buchseite/899332\">facsimile</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup>):<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">[3]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">[4]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">[5]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">[6]</a></sup><dl><dd><span class=\"Latn e-quotation\" lang=\"la\">HIC REQVESC&#xA0;/ ET ALEXSANRA&#xA0;/ <b>PATERESSA</b> QVI V[IX]&#xA0;/ IT ANORO PLUS M[INUS &#x2014;]&#xA0;/ <span class=\"Hebr\" lang=\"he\"><a href=\"/wiki/%D7%A9%D7%9C%D7%95%D7%9D#Hebrew\" title=\"&#x5E9;&#x5DC;&#x5D5;&#x5DD;\">&#x5E9;&#x5DC;&#x5D5;&#x5DD;</a></span>&#x200E;</span><dl><dd>Here rests Alexsanra the <b>fatheress</b>, who lived more or less [&#x2014;] years. Peace.</dd></dl></dd></dl></div></li></ul></li></ol><h4><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Declension\">Declension</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=pateressa&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Declension\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h4><p><a href=\"/wiki/Appendix:Latin_first_declension\" title=\"Appendix:Latin first declension\">First-declension</a> noun.<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r50505018\">.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .corner-header,.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .number-header,.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .case-header{font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .corner-header,.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .number-header{background-color:#549EA0}.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .case-header{background-color:#40E0D0}.mw-parser-output .inflection-table-la .form-cell{backgr